[b][size=12pt]Okay now this is teaching you how to add new shops and custom npc's yes i know there are better ways but this is simple.[/size][/b]

Go to [b]src>com>rs>[/b]

in [b]NPCSpawning.java[/b] file u will see this code

[code=java]World.spawnNPC(554, new WorldTile(3091, 3502, 0), -1, true, true);[/code]

554 = npc id
3091 = x coords
3502 = y coords
0 = npc hight you dont change it and true is weather u want the npc to move or not

now u have added a new npc time to make the shop interface

Now go to [b]src>com>rs>net>decoders>handler[/b] and open [b]NPCHandler.java[/b] and search for

[code=java]else if (npc.getId() == 11270)
ShopsHandler.openShop(player, 19);[/code]

copy it and past it under it NOTE: 11270 is the npc id and 19 is the shop change the 19 to 22 since there are 21 shops already change the npc id to the one u have just made in npcspawning then save and exit

last part go to [b]data>items folder[/b] delete packedShops.s and open up unpackedShops.txt

u see the numbers down the side going from 1 to 21 make a new shop with the next number 22 995 is the shop currency = $ and then shop name then item id then stock amount.

In unpackedshops.txt file there will be a collum on the left with numbers from 1 to 22 these are how many shops there are already on the server. So when making a new shop you would put 23,24,25 ect... 
so in npchandler.java u will be changing this code...

[code=java]else if (npc.getId() == 11270)
ShopsHandler.openShop(player, 19);[/code]

to 23,24,25 and so on.....

save and exit then compile and run new shop and npc.

