[b][size=12pt]Okay this is adding objects to the server also a simpler way of doing this but this is more easy to follow.[/size][/b]

Go to [b]src>com>rs>utils[/b] open NPCSpawning.Java search for.

[code=java]
                World.spawnObject(new WorldObject(17010, 10, 0, 3154, 3484, 0), true);
        [/code]

okay now copy at code and past under it.

17010 = object id
0        = the way it faces
3154   = xcoords
3484   = ycoords

Tip for object faces.

0 = South
1 = West
2 = North
3 = East

World.spawnObject(new WorldObject(17010, 10, 0, 3154, 3484, 0), true);

This just means you are spawning a new object each time you turn the server on.. it's facing "south" and is placed at "3154xcoord 3484ycoord"

save and compile.

