[b][size=12pt]Now this is showing you how to edit prices[/size][/b]

Okay first we are going to edit itemsDefinitions.java you can find it here

[b]src>com>rs>cache>loaders[/b]

once u have opened the file go to the bottom before the last bracket that looks like this } move it down by pressing enter and put this code above it

[code=java]public void setValue(int value) {
	this.value = value;
	}[/code]

then save and exit the file now we are going to edit shops.java you can find this here

[b]src>com>rs>game>player>content[/b]

find this code  

[code=java]public int getBuyPrice(Item item, int dq) {[/code]

and change it to this

[code=java]
	public int getBuyPrice(Item item, int dq) {
		switch (item.getId()) {
		case 1050://item id
			item.getDefinitions().setValue(5000000);//buying price
			break;
		}
		return item.getDefinitions().getValue();
	}
[/code]

okay where it say's "1050" this is the item id so change it to what ever u want
where it says setValue(5000000); this is the item [b]buying price[/b] change it to what ever you like....

okay now once u have change it in the same file find this code

[code=java]public int getSellPrice(Item item, int dq) {[/code]

it should be right under the one u just edited and change it to this

[code=java]
	public int getSellPrice(Item item, int dq) {
		switch (item.getId()) {
		case 1050://item id
			item.getDefinitions().setValue(5000000);//selling price
			break;
		}
		return item.getDefinitions().getValue() / 2;
	}[/code]

same this as abouve change the "1050" to the item u wish to change price of but this time it is the [b]selling price[/b] file and save it then compile and your done.

[img]http://www.upload.ee/image/2184690/shop.png[/img]

to add multiple items at once insted of adding every item in one by one do it like this.

[code=java]
                case 1050:
                        item.getDefinitions().setValue(95000000);
                        break;
                case 11726:
                        item.getDefinitions().setValue(10);
                        break;
                case 11728:
                        item.getDefinitions().setValue(15);
                        break;
                }[/code]

                case 11728:
                        item.getDefinitions().setValue(15);
                        break;

this means 11728 is the item id and it is worth 15gp's... save you from hard coding everything item in

save and compile.

