[size=12pt][b] Simple way of changing and adding new shop currency's[/b][/size]

Okay first we want to add a new currency to the server so we are going to open [b]Shops.java[/b]

this can be found here [b]src>com>rs>game>player>content[/b]

where you see this code here

[code=java]	public static final int COINS = 995;[/code]

When u click on a items in a shop it will have a server message saying how much its worth and what currency it is for this case it is Coins server message would say something like item cost 500,000.000 Coins. 

So copy the code and where it says COINS change it to your currency name e.g. SANTA_HAT or DRAGON_BOOT then the item id so 995 for coins and 1050 for santa hat and dragon boots are 11733 ect...

If your currency has a space in it you must put a _ there insted of a space for it to compile with no errors.

now you have added your currency save and exit time to add this currency to a new shop so go to Data>items folder and delete packedshops.s and edit unpackedshops.txt

Where it says "22 995 false - range shop - 1050 1000"

22 is the shop number 995 is the currenct false lets the npc walk - shop name - item id - shop stock  ect... change the 995 to your new currency you just made and save comple and play :) here is my test so you can all see

[img]http://www.upload.ee/image/2220360/shop_currency.png[/img]

